Two of the suspects were arrested in connection with the cocaine discovery.
The third, a Mexican, was arrested for the confiscated marijuana.
All three are threatened with life imprisonment as a maximum sentence, officials said.
Eight such tunnels have been discovered since 2006, according to a press conference in San Diego.
