George Kerevan: Separation of Europe gives Scots a choice
A new day, a new horror story about independence.
This time we are warned that an independent Scotland is necessary to join the Schengen area as a condition for EU membership.
That provides the keyword for stories about passport controls in Berwick and a barbed-wire border along the Hadrian Wall.
Indeed, the Strathclyde template pointed out the potential economic benefits that would bring more freedom of travel in the rest of Europe, but, as expected, this did not play a role in the headlines.
Nor has anyone mentioned that EU member states often turn their strict rules when it is more favourable to them.
